 
 
 
 (1) look for and remove some files
 $ rm `find . -name ".DS_Store"`
 $ rm `find . -name ".preferences.xml"`

 (2) modify the PATH environment variable
 $ cd ~
 $ emacs .bashrc (save: control x + control s; exit: control x + control c)
 $ source ~/.bashrc (refresh .bashrc)
 
 (3) 
 $ cd ~/Document/workspaceV2/sireum-bakar
 $ git status (check any change status of the project sireum-bakar)
 
 (4) create soft link
 $ ln -s ~/Downloads/gnat2xml .  (create a link in current directory to gnat2xml)
  
 (5) 
 $ ls -lah 
 
 .preferences
 
 (6) compile the .rst file to pdf
To compile the documentation just do the following under
sireum-bakar-internal/sireum-bakar-doc/src/main/resources:

* HTML:$ make html
* PDF: $ make latexpdf

Note that you need to have sphinx installed (I use macports' py27-sphinx).


 
